timelineItems.name: SacRepublicFC
timelineItems.text: 10' Entering the 10th minute, the score remains 0-0, but already turning into a physical match #SJvSRFC

timelineItems.name: SacRepublicFC
timelineItems.text: 13' Alvarez with cross, but easily picked off by SJ defender. #SJvSRFC remains 0-0

timelineItems.comment: Match ends, San Jose Earthquakes 2, Sacramento Republic FC 1.

timelineItems.name: SacRepublicFC
timelineItems.text: Republic FC falls 2-1, plays with 10 man team final 11 minutes. #SJvSRFC

timelineItems.name: San Jose Earthquakes
timelineItems.text: Next time you get to see the Quakes at home? June 28 at Stanford vs. @LAGalaxy. Be there: http://t.co/uEfhWDV1Wc #Quakes74 #CaliClasico

timelineItems.name: SacRepublicFC
timelineItems.text: Preki (paraphrase): Tough team, our partner. We made it tough for them. Despite loss still lots of positives from tonight. #SJvSRFC

timelineItems.name: SacRepublicFC
timelineItems.text: .@justinbraun17 "Unfortunately, we weren't able to win. But that's soccer...We can play with anyone and we showed that tonight." #SJvSRFC

timelineItems.text: ONLINE STREAM IS BACK UP! Available via http://t.co/L60CiVSgzw #SJvSRFC #USOC2014
